l the layout how to setup.  It will setup the slice height and how many slices are visible."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"There are two supported modes: autoScroll on\/off"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"When autoScroll is true, the slices are automatically scrolled.  Subscribe to the delgate and listen for the scrolled callback, when you get it send another slice of text","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"When autoScroll is false, you can drive the slices and how they look on the screen.  You can send all the slices at once or send one at a time and animate it onto the screen at the current time.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ultralitesdk.UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout"},"doc://ultralitesdk.UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout/AutoScroller":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/ultralitesdk.UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller","role":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AutoScroller","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller","title":"ScrollLayout.AutoScroller","abstract":[{"text":"AutoScroller is a utility class to send a large known block of predfined text to the glasses to be smoothly scrolled.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"This is simlar to what is seen on a teleprompter or in movie credits.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This class was written using the "},{"code":"ScrollLayout","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" commands and is nothing more than a convience class."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Everything used this class can be written from the public SDK."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It scrolls the text much like a teleprompter would with basic commands to pause and resume the scrolling.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The duration (speed) of the scrolling can be modified while scrolling by seting the ","type":"text"},{"code":"duration","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" property."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It can support any language that the font supports.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If the content is not known up front, or subject to change, this is the utility class will not work (use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"LiveText"},{"type":"text","text":" instance instead)."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AutoScroller","kind":"identifier"}]}}}